<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1833,2040]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1833,1859]" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[484,551,1833,1859]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,505,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-140@2.[151,1436,486,1925]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, holotype male. 1. Forewing; 2. Hindwing; 3. Genitalia, dorsal view; 4. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 5–6. Hypandrium; 7. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) basal one-fifth with a slightly curved greyish white stripe; radial fork with branches diverging at an angle about 90°. Epiproct (
<figureCitation box="[743,844,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,505,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-140@2.[151,1436,486,1925]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, holotype male. 1. Forewing; 2. Hindwing; 3. Genitalia, dorsal view; 4. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 5–6. Hypandrium; 7. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Figs 3–4</figureCitation>
) nearly triangular, pointed at apex, with a nearly Ushaped sclerotized area at base; hypandrium (
<figureCitation box="[672,775,1905,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1951,1975]" captionTargetBox="[171,1415,505,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-140@2.[151,1436,486,1925]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, holotype male. 1. Forewing; 2. Hindwing; 3. Genitalia, dorsal view; 4. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 5–6. Hypandrium; 7. Phallosome. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877305/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Figs 5–6</figureCitation>
) with a broad ridge at middle. Female. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1358,1427,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,194,1193]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,1203]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–15. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, paratype female. 8. Forewing; 9. Hindwing; 10–11. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 12–13. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 14–15. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) with a grayish white striped marking at one-fifth base; radial fork with branches diverging at an angle about 90°. Pigmented area of subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[556,684,1977,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,194,1193]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,1203]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–15. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, paratype female. 8. Forewing; 9. Hindwing; 10–11. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 12–13. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 14–15. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Figs 14–15</figureCitation>
) roughly T-shaped, distally flat; dorsal valve (
<figureCitation box="[1205,1334,1977,2003]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–15" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1227,1251]" captionTargetBox="[163,1428,194,1193]" captionTargetId="figure-27@3.[151,1436,181,1203]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–15. Ceratostigma gracile Li, 2002, paratype female. 8. Forewing; 9. Hindwing; 10–11. Epiproct and paraproct, dorsal view; 12–13. Gonapophyses, ventral view; 14–15. Subgenital plate, ventral view. ep: epiproct; pp: paraproct; vv: ventral valve; dv: dorsal valve; ev: external valve." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6877307" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6877307/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="197">Figs 12–13</figureCitation>
) anterior one-third with a slightly sclerotized area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
