<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="198" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,150,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, 2002:" authorityYear="1595" box="[326,576,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Psocidae" genus="Ceratostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[326,576,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">Ceratostigma gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lienhard" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[739,963,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Psocidae" genus="Ceratostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostigmatum">
<emphasis box="[739,963,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">C. macrostigmatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in male forewing basal one-fifth with a slightly curved greyish white stripe; radial fork with branches diverging at an angle less than 90°; epiproct nearly triangular, pointed at apex, with a nearly U-shaped sclerotized area at base; hypandrium with a broad ridge in the medium. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Li, 2002:" authorityYear="1595" box="[258,377,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Psocidae" genus="Ceratostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracilis">
<emphasis box="[258,377,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">C. gracilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lienhard" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[683,904,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Psocidae" genus="Ceratostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostigmatum">
<emphasis box="[683,904,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="198">C. macrostigmatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the hypandrium rounded apically, while the hypandrium of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lienhard" authorityYear="2003" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Yang" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[324,543,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Psocidae" genus="Ceratostigma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Psocodea" pageId="2" pageNumber="198" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrostigmatum">
